Tapirs consume aquatic vegetation and the leaves, buds, twigs, and fruits of low-growing terrestrial plants, but in any particular habitat they eat mainly the green shoots of the most common prowsing plants. They also graze for food, and at times they have been known to damage young corn and other grains.
